prefix: You are an expert in number theory. Solve the following problem.
problem_prompt: You are an expert in number theory. Solve the following problem. You are given that $3^{400}\equiv 1\pmod{1000}$. What are the last three digits of $3^{12000}$?
solution:
The last three digits are the same as the remainder when divided by $1000$.

$3^{400}\equiv 1\pmod{1000}\implies 3^{12000}=(3^{400})^{30}\equiv 1^{30}=1\pmod{1000}$.

Thus, the last three digits are $\boxed{001}$.
gpt_response:
Since we have $3^{400}\equiv 1\pmod{1000}$, we know that $3^{400}, 3^{800}, 3^{1200}, \ldots$ leaves a remainder of 1 when divided by 1000. 

So, $3^{12000}= (3^{400})^{30}\equiv 1^{30}\equiv 1\pmod{1000}$.

Therefore, the last three digits of $3^{12000}$ are 001.
